Regression test for the L-1 lockdown extension of
`polymorphismResidual` (saw-central/src/SAWCentral/Prover/Exporter.hs)
to a full term-tree walk.

Background. The original 2026-04-23 D3 check used `asPiList` to
walk only the outer pi-spine. A type like
`((α : sort 1) → α) → β` has its `sort 1` binder inside an
argument type — `asPiList` returned `[(f : (α : sort 1) → α)]`
and the `highSortParam` predicate looked at `f`'s type which
*contains* but isn't itself a sort, so the residual escaped and
`translateSort` silently collapsed it.

Audit S-1 flagged this as the highest-priority real soundness
gap. L-1 replaces the spine walk with an `IORef`-memoised full
term traversal that catches every Pi binder anywhere in the type
term.

This test pins the nested case: a term whose argument type
contains a `(a : sort 1) → ...` binder. Pre-L-1 SAW translated
this silently; post-L-1 SAW exits non-zero with the same
"Refusing to translate a term that binds a universe strictly
above Type 0" diagnostic the existing
`test_lean_soundness_polymorphic` pins for the outer-spine case.
